§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A ∈ 𝗦^n$ (i.e., $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ and symmetric). ⦉

  ‖ $A$ is ❬positive definite❭ if, for all $x ≠ 0 ∈ 𝗥^{d}$,
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x^⊤ A x > 0. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ $A$ is ❬positive semidefinite❭ (or ❬nonnegative definite❭) if,
    for all $x ∈ 𝗥^{d}$
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x^⊤ A x ≥ 0. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the set of positive definite $d$ by
    $d$ matrices by $𝗦_{++}^d$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the set of  positive semidefinite $d$
    by $d$ matrices by $𝗦_{+}^d$. ⦉
⦉

